# Task

Define the ToBamlValue trait and implement for all primitive types.

## File to Create/Modify
`baml-bridge/crates/bridge/src/lib.rs` (or new file `to_value.rs`)

## Trait Definition

```rust
/// Convert a typed value to BamlValue for serialization.
/// This is the inverse of BamlValueConvert.
/// 
/// Implementations must produce values that BamlValueConvert::try_from_baml_value can parse back.
pub trait ToBamlValue {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> baml_types::BamlValue;
}
```

## All 10 BamlValue Variants to Handle

The trait must produce these BamlValue variants correctly:
1. `BamlValue::String(String)` - from String, &str
2. `BamlValue::Int(i64)` - from i8, i16, i32, i64, u8, u16, u32
3. `BamlValue::Float(f64)` - from f32, f64
4. `BamlValue::Bool(bool)` - from bool
5. `BamlValue::Null` - from Option::None
6. `BamlValue::List(Vec<BamlValue>)` - from Vec<T>
7. `BamlValue::Map(BamlMap<String, BamlValue>)` - from HashMap/BTreeMap
8. `BamlValue::Enum(enum_name, variant_string)` - from unit enums
9. `BamlValue::Class(class_name, field_map)` - from structs
10. `BamlValue::Media(BamlMedia)` - special handling

## Primitive Implementations

```rust
impl ToBamlValue for String {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::String(self.clone()) }
}

impl ToBamlValue for &str {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::String((*self).to_string()) }
}

impl ToBamlValue for bool {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::Bool(*self) }
}

// All integer types
impl ToBamlValue for i32 {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::Int(*self as i64) }
}
// ... i8, i16, i64, u8, u16, u32, u64 (u64 may overflow i64)

impl ToBamlValue for f32 {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::Float(*self as f64) }
}

impl ToBamlValue for f64 {
    fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue { BamlValue::Float(*self) }
}
```

## Testing Strategy

```rust
#[test]
fn test_primitive_to_baml_value() {
    assert_eq!("hello".to_baml_value(), BamlValue::String("hello".into()));
    assert_eq!(42i32.to_baml_value(), BamlValue::Int(42));
    assert_eq!(3.14f64.to_baml_value(), BamlValue::Float(3.14));
    assert_eq!(true.to_baml_value(), BamlValue::Bool(true));
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
1. ToBamlValue trait defined and exported from bridge crate
2. All Rust primitives implemented (String, bool, numeric types)
3. Unit tests for each primitive type
4. All 10 BamlValue variants documented
